
## üé® **Iron Meridian Web Style & UI Design Guide**

---

### üìÅ 1. **Visual Philosophy**

* **Dark, clean aesthetic** grounded in fantasy UI tone ‚Äî similar to magical grimoires, arcane terminals, or guild archives.
* Primary contrast through **light text on dark backgrounds**, not through color noise.
* Accent colors (gold/yellow) used **sparingly for guidance**, not decoration.

---

### üåà 2. **Color Usage Guidelines**

| Context          | Color Source            | Notes                                       |
| ---------------- | ----------------------- | ------------------------------------------- |
| Page Background  | `--bg-dark`             | Full-page backdrop, calm matte black        |
| Card Backgrounds | `--bg-card`             | Surface panels for text/interactive content |
| Primary Text     | `--text`                | Always highly legible, off-white/light grey |
| Highlights/Focus | `--accent`              | Only for buttons, badge states, titles      |
| Borders/Dividers | `--border-light`        | Low contrast edges, subtle lines            |
| Muted Meta Text  | `#bbbbbb` @ 85% opacity | Used for timestamps, labels, soft info      |

---

### üß± 3. **Structural Elements**

#### ‚úÖ Cards

* Use `.card`, `.report`, `.player-card`
* `border-left: 3px solid #555` for grounded tone
* **No strong glows or heavy shadows by default**
* Hover lift: `transform: translateY(-2px);`

#### ‚úÖ Buttons

* Use `.btn`, `.button`
* Default background: `#2c2c2c`, border: `var(--border-light)`
* Text: white always, no gradient
* On hover: `border-color: var(--accent);`

#### ‚úÖ Sidebar

* Use `#1f1f1f` background
* Active or hover state: `background-color: rgba(255, 217, 102, 0.15);`
* No abrupt color inversion

---

### üîé 4. **Typography Standards**

| Element   | Rule                                                               |
| --------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------ |
| Headings  | `clamp(1.25rem, 2vw, 2rem)` ‚Äî no all-caps, color: `--accent-light` |
| Body Text | `--text` @ `1rem` or `0.95rem`, `line-height: 1.6`                 |
| Meta Info | `.text-meta`: `0.85rem`, `#bbbbbb`, 85% opacity                    |
| Buttons   | `bold`, `uppercase: false`, font-size consistent per screen size   |

---

### üîÅ 5. **Relational Inputs (Your Key UX Rule)**

#### ‚úÖ Linking Relational Items (e.g. Add Loot to Quest)

**Absolutely follow this UI rule:**

> ‚ÄúAll relational additions (like attaching loot, assigning a location, selecting faction, etc.) **must** use a searchable dropdown input. Never use text input fields, ID codes, or modals.‚Äù

#### Use:

* `<select>` elements upgraded via **JavaScript-enhanced dropdowns**
* Preferred Libraries: `Tom Select`, `Select2`, `Choices.js`
* Must support:

  * Type-to-search
  * Clearable tags
  * Multi-select where applicable
  * Grouping or tagging (optional)

#### Example (Tom Select):

```html
<select id="specialLoot" class="form-control" placeholder="Search or select cursed items...">
  <option value="cursed-amulet">Cursed Amulet of Mirthless Sleep</option>
  <option value="blackened-ring">Blackened Ring of Control</option>
  <option value="blight-coin">Blight Coin</option>
</select>
<script>
  new TomSelect("#specialLoot", {
    create: false,
    maxItems: 1,
    allowEmptyOption: true,
    placeholder: "Select an item...",
  });
</script>
```

---

### üîß 6. **Form UX Preferences**

* **Inputs** use `.form-control` with:

  * Dark backgrounds (`--bg-card`)
  * White text
  * Gold border highlight on focus
* **Dropdowns only** for linking structured data (players, items, locations)
* **Text inputs** reserved for freeform notes or descriptions

---

### üìå 7. **Component Rules**

| Component        | Rules                                                               |
| ---------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| Sidebar Nav      | Icon + label, consistent padding, no shrink on smaller screens      |
| Player Panel     | `.player-card` style, left border highlight optional                |
| Quest Cards      | Use `.badge` for status (Main, Guild, Side), with `badge-info` etc. |
| Location Tracker | All dropdown assigned tags (not typed)                              |
| Backstories      | Use `<textarea>` or Markdown input                                  |

---

### ü™Ñ 8. **Visual Accessibility Tips**

* Minimum contrast ratio: **WCAG AA (4.5:1)** for all text elements
* Never rely on **color alone** to convey information (e.g. use tags + icons)
* Support keyboard navigation for all dropdown and list elements
* Large hit areas: min `40x40px` for touch targets

---

### üß© 9. **Optional Nice-to-Haves**

| Feature                    | Style Recommendation                                                |
| -------------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| Light/Dark toggle          | Preserve dark mode as default                                       |
| Hover tooltips for icons   | Use `title=""` or JS tooltips for descriptions                      |
| Tags for quests or players | Use `.badge` with `.badge-sm` and `.badge-accent` where relevant    |
| ‚Äú+ Add‚Äù actions            | Always show as `btn` with inline label/icon (never hidden or modal) |

